
Location of Pova&lt;U+017E&gt;sk&lt;U+00E1&gt; Bystrica District in the Tren&lt;U+010D&gt;&lt;U+00ED&gt;n Region

Horn&lt;U+00FD&gt; Lieskov is a village and municipality in Pova&lt;U+017E&gt;sk&lt;U+00E1&gt; Bystrica District in the Tren&lt;U+010D&gt;&lt;U+00ED&gt;n Region of north-western Slovakia.
History
In historical records the village was first mentioned in 1330.
Geography
The municipality lies at an altitude of 370 metres and covers an area of 4.897 km&lt;U+00B2&gt;. It has a population of about 373 people.
